Prior art and attribution
-------------------------

framedrag's feed catalog is derived from pfBlockerNG
(https://github.com/pfBlockerNG/pfBlockerNG), created by BBcan177 and
maintained with Rubicon Communications, LLC. pfBlockerNG is licensed
under the Apache License, Version 2.0. A decade of feed curation, the
quality tiering (PRI1 through PRI5), and the catalog itself
(pfblockerng_feeds.json) are pfBlockerNG's work; framedrag tracks that
catalog rather than forking it.

The underlying technique, null-routing curated IP reputation feeds,
descends from Paul Vixie and Dave Rand's RBL (1997), which was
originally distributed as a BGP feed that black-holed spammer IPs, a
practice known as Remotely Triggered Black Hole (RTBH) filtering.
framedrag is that idea, at the edge, without BGP.
